{{infobox Onsen | Name = Yoshii Onsen (吉井温泉) | image = Yoshii onsen.JPG | Comment = | Location = {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Ukiha City|ja|うきは市|12=draft|12=draft}} | Access = Rail: From the {{ill|Kyūdai Main Line|ja|久大本線|12=draft|12=draft}} at {{ill|Chikugo Yoshii Station|ja|筑後吉井駅|12=draft|12=draft}}, take a {{ill|taxi|ja|タクシー|12=draft|12=draft}} for about 7 minutes. | Spring Quality = {{ill|Simple Hot Springs|lt=Simple Hot Spring|ja|単純温泉|1=Simple Hot Springs|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Bicarbonate and Ferric Hydroxide Hot Spring|ja|炭酸水酸化鉄泉|12=draft|12=draft}} | Spring Temperature = 36 – 42°C | Flow Rate = | pH = | Classification of Liquid Nature = | Classification of Osmotic Pressure = | Number of Lodging Facilities = 3 | Total Capacity = | Annual Number of Bathers = | Statistical Year = | External Links = | Special Notes = }}
'''Yoshii Onsen''' (吉井温泉) is a {{ill|hot spring|ja|温泉|1=Onsen|1=Onsen|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Ukiha City|ja|うきは市|12=draft|12=draft}} (formerly part of {{ill|Chikugo Province|ja|筑後国|12=draft|12=draft}}).
== Hot Spring Quality == * {{ill|Bicarbonate and Ferric Hydroxide Hot Spring|ja|炭酸水酸化鉄泉|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Simple Hot Springs|lt=Simple Hot Spring|ja|単純温泉|1=Simple Hot Springs|12=draft|12=draft}} ** {{ill|Source Temperature|ja|源泉温度|12=draft|12=draft}} 36–42°C
== Hot Spring Town == The hot spring town is located on the left bank of the {{ill|Chikugo River|ja|筑後川|12=draft|12=draft}}, where inns and day-use hot spring facilities can be found.<ref name="env">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.env.go.jp/nature/onsen/area/pdf/hoyo_056.pdf|title=吉井温泉 国民保養温泉地計画書|website={{ill|Ministry of the Environment|ja|環境省|1=Ministry of the Environment (Japan)|lt=Ministry of the Environment|12=draft|12=draft}}|accessdate=2024-11-29}}</ref> On the opposite bank of the Chikugo River lies {{ill|Hara-Tsuru Onsen|ja|原鶴温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Like Hara-Tsuru Onsen, the hot spring town is also renowned for its specialties in {{ill|cormorant fishing|ja|鵜飼い|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|ayu|ja|鮎|12=draft|12=draft}} cuisine.
== History == The hot spring was first opened in {{ill|1956|ja|1956|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is said to have been discovered through a divine revelation, earning it the alternative name {{ill|Kami no Se Onsen|ja|神の瀬温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Twelve years later, on November 19, 1968 (Showa 43), by notification No. 451 issued by the {{ill|Ministry of Health and Welfare|ja|厚生労働省|lt=Ministry of Health and Welfare|12=draft|12=draft}}, it was designated as a {{ill|National Public Resort Hot Spring Area|ja|国民保養温泉地|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Access == * Rail: About 7 minutes by {{ill|taxi|ja|タクシー|12=draft|12=draft}} from {{ill|Chikugo Yoshii Station|ja|筑後吉井駅|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Kyūdai Main Line|ja|久大本線|12=draft|12=draft}}.
