{{infobox Onsen | Name = Yoshii Onsen (吉井温泉) | image = Yoshii onsen.JPG | Comment = | Location = [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]] [[:en:Ukiha, Fukuoka|Ukiha City]] | Access = Rail: From the [[:en:Kyūdai Main Line|Kyūdai Main Line]] at [[:en:Chikugo-Yoshii Station|Chikugo Yoshii Station]], take a [[:en:Taxi|taxi]] for about 7 minutes. | Spring Quality = {{ill|Simple Hot Springs|lt=Simple Hot Spring|ja|単純温泉|1=Simple Hot Springs|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Simple Hot Springs|13=User:Immanuelle/Simple Hot Springs|qq=}}, {{ill|Bicarbonate and Ferric Hydroxide Hot Spring|ja|炭酸水酸化鉄泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bicarbonate and Ferric Hydroxide Hot Spring|qq=}} | Spring Temperature = 36 – 42°C | Flow Rate = | pH = | Classification of Liquid Nature = | Classification of Osmotic Pressure = | Number of Lodging Facilities = 3 | Total Capacity = | Annual Number of Bathers = | Statistical Year = | External Links = | Special Notes = }}
'''Yoshii Onsen''' (吉井温泉) is a [[:en:Onsen|Onsen]] located in [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]] [[:en:Ukiha, Fukuoka|Ukiha City]] (formerly part of [[:en:Chikugo Province|Chikugo Province]]).
== Hot Spring Quality == * {{ill|Bicarbonate and Ferric Hydroxide Hot Spring|ja|炭酸水酸化鉄泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bicarbonate and Ferric Hydroxide Hot Spring|qq=}} * {{ill|Simple Hot Springs|lt=Simple Hot Spring|ja|単純温泉|1=Simple Hot Springs|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Simple Hot Springs|13=User:Immanuelle/Simple Hot Springs|qq=}} ** {{ill|Source Temperature|ja|源泉温度|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Source Temperature|qq=}} 36–42°C
== Hot Spring Town == The hot spring town is located on the left bank of the [[:en:Chikugo River|Chikugo River]], where inns and day-use hot spring facilities can be found.<ref name="env">{{Cite web|和書|url=https://www.env.go.jp/nature/onsen/area/pdf/hoyo_056.pdf|title=吉井温泉 国民保養温泉地計画書|website=[[:en:Ministry of the Environment (Japan)|Ministry of the Environment]]|accessdate=2024-11-29}}</ref> On the opposite bank of the Chikugo River lies {{ill|Hara-Tsuru Onsen|ja|原鶴温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hara-Tsuru Onsen|qq=}}.
Like Hara-Tsuru Onsen, the hot spring town is also renowned for its specialties in [[:en:Cormorant fishing|cormorant fishing]] and {{ill|ayu|ja|鮎|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ayu|qq=}} cuisine.
== History == The hot spring was first opened in {{ill|1956|ja|1956|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1956|qq=}}. It is said to have been discovered through a divine revelation, earning it the alternative name {{ill|Kami no Se Onsen|ja|神の瀬温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kami no Se Onsen|qq=}}.
Twelve years later, on November 19, 1968 (Showa 43), by notification No. 451 issued by the [[:en:Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare|Ministry of Health and Welfare]], it was designated as a {{ill|National Public Resort Hot Spring Area|ja|国民保養温泉地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/National Public Resort Hot Spring Area|qq=}}.
== Access == * Rail: About 7 minutes by [[:en:Taxi|taxi]] from [[:en:Chikugo-Yoshii Station|Chikugo Yoshii Station]] on the [[:en:Kyūdai Main Line|Kyūdai Main Line]].
